AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - AFRICA (01): ZAMBIA (LUSAKA) DOMESTIC, OIE
****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 31 Mar 2021
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2022 [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=51452


African swine fever virus, Zambia
------------------------------
General information
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 1 Mar 2022
Confirmed: 4 Mar 2022
Reported: 30 Mar 2022
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 1 Sep 2021
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location 1: Chilanga District, Mapepe Vet Camp, Kafue, Lusaka
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Mar 2022
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Swine / 16 / 16 / 16 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak location 2 Kafue District, Shantumbu Veterinary Camp, Kafue, Lusaka
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Mar 2022
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Swine / 15 / 11 / 0 / 15 / 0 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Affected pig populations were of all ages in a commercial management system.

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures applied: disinfection, movement control, quarantine, selective killing and disposal, traceability, surveillance outside the restricted zone, surveillance within the restricted zone

Additional measures: stamping out

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Research Institute (CVRI) (National Laboratory) / swine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 4 Mar 2022 / positive

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

